WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:19.749 --> 00:22.652
Come on, slowpoke!

00:22.685 --> 00:25.356
-Is that all you've got?
-Hey, hey!

00:25.389 --> 00:27.590
-Come on.
-Hey!

00:28.859 --> 00:31.628
I told you,
you have to master one.

00:31.662 --> 00:36.867
Yeah, blame it
on the engine...

00:38.768 --> 00:40.403
Hey, wait up!

00:46.542 --> 00:49.479
Alright, alright, you win.

00:49.512 --> 00:52.315
I'm sorry. What? I didn't hear.

00:52.349 --> 00:55.186
I said, you win.

00:57.853 --> 01:01.624
-This is a bad idea.
-Yes, it is.

01:01.657 --> 01:04.962
No, really.
We've been gone too long.

01:04.995 --> 01:06.830
What are you worried about?

01:06.863 --> 01:09.366
Your sister isn't going to think
anything is going on.

01:09.399 --> 01:11.669
Look, this has been fun

01:11.702 --> 01:13.237
but this karma
is going to come back

01:13.270 --> 01:16.372
and bite us in the ass, man.

01:16.405 --> 01:20.478
Fine, we'll head back, but...

01:23.380 --> 01:24.581
One more time?

01:25.414 --> 01:27.651
And that's it.

01:27.684 --> 01:29.987
-Deal?
-Unbelievable.

01:30.020 --> 01:31.789
Yeah. Let's do it.

01:35.559 --> 01:37.628
Hey, Maggie, watch this! Yeah!

01:39.363 --> 01:42.967
Vince! Vince!

01:43.000 --> 01:44.702
Vince!

01:47.771 --> 01:49.307
Vince!

01:51.741 --> 01:54.478
-Vince!
-Help, Maggie, help!

01:54.511 --> 01:56.413
My God. What happened?

01:56.446 --> 01:57.447
-Maggie.
-You okay?

01:58.714 --> 02:01.818
Here, take my arm. Here.!

02:04.553 --> 02:06.923
Maggie?

02:08.991 --> 02:11.762
Maggie!

02:29.624 --> 02:33.691
TOXIC SHARK

02:35.282 --> 02:38.782
Subrip: Pix

03:31.475 --> 03:32.876
<i>Hola, mamacita.</i>

03:35.978 --> 03:37.747
And you thought
this was gonna be a bad idea.

03:37.781 --> 03:39.483
No, this is a bad idea.

03:39.515 --> 03:40.783
This place looks like
the first episode

03:40.817 --> 03:42.619
of one of those
horrible dating shows.

03:42.651 --> 03:44.520
Come on, man, you said
you wanted to do something

03:44.554 --> 03:45.889
to get your mind off your ex.

03:45.922 --> 03:47.791
Plus, none of us
ever liked her, anyway.

03:47.823 --> 03:50.393
-She was toxic.
-A singles' retreat though, man?

03:50.426 --> 03:53.030
I was thinking, like,
Vegas or Tijuana even.

03:53.062 --> 03:55.566
Vegas is where you met Eden,
stupid.

03:55.598 --> 03:57.567
No! No Vegas trip.

03:57.601 --> 03:59.803
This is Puerto Rico, baby!

03:59.835 --> 04:01.704
I can't believe
you're bitchin' about this.

04:01.738 --> 04:03.774
Do you know how long it took me
to save up for this trip?

04:03.806 --> 04:06.410
The phone company does not
give out Christmas bonuses.

04:06.442 --> 04:07.944
Really,
this coming from the guy

04:07.977 --> 04:09.879
who hasn't paid a phone bill in,
what, eight years?

04:09.912 --> 04:12.749
Well, you fix the lines,
you don't pay the fines.

04:12.782 --> 04:15.452
-I've never heard that before.
-What're you guys talking about?

04:15.484 --> 04:18.821
I mean, look at this place.
This place is beautiful!

04:18.853 --> 04:21.656
Yo, anyway, let's unload.
Yeah, I need to hit the gym.

04:21.690 --> 04:23.994
My pecs are feeling kinda soft
from the travel?

04:24.027 --> 04:25.696
There's no gym, dum-dum.

04:25.729 --> 04:27.631
The only thing soft
on this island is your brain.

04:27.664 --> 04:30.000
Wait, what? You said
this was a fitness retreat.

04:30.032 --> 04:32.835
It's a off-the-grid,
rugged, campsite thingy, man

04:32.869 --> 04:34.871
just like we did
when we were Boy Scouts

04:34.905 --> 04:39.743
but with girls,
snorkels and girls.

04:39.775 --> 04:41.677
How'd I get
talked into this again?

04:41.710 --> 04:46.417
Look, brah, girls and boats,
your two favorite things.

04:46.450 --> 04:48.852
And if you're lucky, you're
bound to go down on one of 'em.

04:48.885 --> 04:50.454
Yeah, bro!

04:54.825 --> 04:57.061
Whatever. Let's check in.
It's reality-show time.

04:58.628 --> 05:01.131
Hey, think of it this way?

05:01.164 --> 05:03.167
It's a way to get your mind off
of, what's her name?

05:03.200 --> 05:05.869
Eden. My ex-girlfriend's name
is Eden, Ryan.

05:05.902 --> 05:07.104
-Yeah.
-Good job.

05:11.607 --> 05:12.742
Hi there.

05:14.176 --> 05:15.746
Watch your step.

05:19.181 --> 05:21.884
This place is beautiful!

05:21.917 --> 05:23.987
-I like your shirt.
-Thanks. We sell them.

05:24.020 --> 05:25.889
-Did you get the catalog?
-Yeah.

05:25.922 --> 05:28.025
You know, the guys in here
just got lucky

05:28.058 --> 05:30.127
now that you girls arrived.

05:30.160 --> 05:32.862
Great line.

05:34.698 --> 05:36.532
Come on, Eden, he's charming.

05:36.566 --> 05:39.102
Yeah, yeah. Charming.

05:39.135 --> 05:41.104
Alright. You girls
are in the Gutanna group.

05:41.136 --> 05:43.105
Your cabin is just north
over the hill.

05:43.138 --> 05:45.809
Gutanna group? Do we get
color-coded buffs, too?

05:47.176 --> 05:49.078
Like, on "Survivor?" No?

05:49.112 --> 05:51.047
Am I the only one
that still watches that show?

05:51.080 --> 05:52.549
Yeah.

05:52.582 --> 05:54.017
You know, this place
is run by Reese.

05:54.049 --> 05:55.852
He's like a fitness superstar.

05:55.886 --> 05:58.087
Yeah, we read about that
on the website.

05:58.121 --> 05:59.256
When are we gonna eat?

05:59.289 --> 06:00.824
-I don't know.
-I'm hungry.

06:00.857 --> 06:03.126
But we got a chef
from New York.

06:03.159 --> 06:04.962
He's really good.

06:04.994 --> 06:06.662
-Here?
-Yeah, here.

06:06.696 --> 06:09.265
Just settle in, and in an hour
there's gonna be lunch.

06:09.299 --> 06:13.070
It's gonna be, like, fresh crab,
mango kale salad

06:13.102 --> 06:14.670
and something else.
I don't know.

06:14.703 --> 06:16.906
What else is on the menu?

06:16.939 --> 06:18.674
I think this might be
a good time to mention

06:18.708 --> 06:20.210
that I'm allergic to shellfish

06:20.242 --> 06:22.512
and pretty much anything else
from the sea.

06:22.546 --> 06:23.848
Perfect.

06:26.883 --> 06:28.652
Hey, you sure
I can't convince you

06:28.684 --> 06:29.952
to hang out
for a couple of days?

06:29.986 --> 06:31.622
Listen, you like golf, right?

06:31.655 --> 06:32.989
Puerto Rico's got
some of the most gorgeous

06:33.023 --> 06:34.525
golf courses in all the country.

06:34.558 --> 06:35.759
You know, another inspector
might think

06:35.792 --> 06:37.160
you were trying to bribe me,
Reese.

06:37.193 --> 06:38.962
That would mean
I have something to hide

06:38.994 --> 06:41.965
but I passed, right? I passed.
So what's the problem?

06:41.998 --> 06:44.268
The problem is the numerous
complaints by former guests

06:44.301 --> 06:46.003
reporting sudden illnesses
after staying at your...

06:46.035 --> 06:48.170
Come on, that's a bunch of BS.

06:48.203 --> 06:50.806
Listen, like I said, we offer
a highly intensive

06:50.840 --> 06:53.143
physical and spiritual package.

06:53.176 --> 06:55.779
Sometimes the body is
not used to a jolt like that.

06:55.811 --> 06:57.948
Listen, getting sick for
a few days is just part of it.

06:57.980 --> 06:59.582
-Whatever you say.
-They'll recover.

06:59.616 --> 07:01.685
Here. Take this.

07:04.253 --> 07:06.556
-What's this for?
-Water-testing kit.

07:06.590 --> 07:07.958
Better for you to be prepared
when you start hearing

07:07.991 --> 07:09.893
from the lawyers,
I'd test the seawater

07:09.926 --> 07:12.896
every morning if I was you,
before anyone goes swimming.

07:12.929 --> 07:14.198
Let's go.

07:23.873 --> 07:25.209
Have a nice trip.

07:37.087 --> 07:39.823
<i>-Reese, come in. You there?
-Yeah.</i>

07:39.855 --> 07:41.157
<i>You got the lunch figured out
for today?</i>

07:41.191 --> 07:42.359
No, Damiano and Gregory

07:42.391 --> 07:43.893
are supposed to be
working on that.

07:43.926 --> 07:46.095
<i>-If you say so.
-Okay.</i>

07:52.969 --> 07:55.372
Look at this, man. You see this?

07:55.405 --> 07:59.309
All my nets
are ripped to shreds.

07:59.342 --> 08:02.580
I'm just gonna try it
over there one more time.

08:05.047 --> 08:06.282
I don't get it.

08:06.316 --> 08:08.150
This is the third net
today already.

08:08.184 --> 08:10.287
-That's messed up.
-Yeah, this ocean stinks, man.

08:10.320 --> 08:13.323
I'm telling you, man, it's
the same thing all over again.

08:13.355 --> 08:15.725
And what's the smell?

08:15.758 --> 08:17.259
I mean, is it you, me?

08:17.292 --> 08:19.996
I can't even tell anymore
if it's a fish.

08:20.030 --> 08:21.999
-Geez.
-Well, it's not me.

08:22.032 --> 08:23.900
I mean, if you showered
more than once, maybe...

08:23.933 --> 08:25.202
Come on, Greg. Shut up.

08:25.234 --> 08:28.638
I used to be a chef in New York,
you know?

08:28.672 --> 08:31.273
This is useless, man. We're
not gonna catch anything here.

08:31.306 --> 08:33.342
I cook the fish,
I'm not supposed to be, like

08:33.376 --> 08:36.412
ass-deep in this ocean
tryin' to catch them.

08:36.446 --> 08:39.349
A week ago,
all this area was full of fish

08:39.381 --> 08:42.818
and right now, what,
they flew south or something?

08:42.851 --> 08:45.154
-I don't know.
-You know, it's just like...

08:45.187 --> 08:47.723
-What the hell?
-What?

08:47.757 --> 08:50.327
I stepped on a sea urchin
or something.

08:50.359 --> 08:53.162
I'm done with this.
You know what? I'm done!

08:53.196 --> 08:55.798
-What the hell, man? That's it!
-Dude, what are we cooking?

08:55.831 --> 08:57.667
You know what?
Make some tuna salad.

08:57.700 --> 09:00.671
I'm done. I'm not getting
paid enough for this crap.

09:00.704 --> 09:02.973
You know? That's it. I'm going.

09:03.005 --> 09:05.875
Come on, help me! Greg!

09:05.908 --> 09:07.878
Hey, come on! Help!
My eyes! It burns!

09:07.911 --> 09:09.747
Come on, help!

09:34.870 --> 09:36.472
Do your phones work?
I have no signal.

09:36.505 --> 09:38.274
It was working fine in San Juan.

09:38.307 --> 09:42.745
Well, we are on a small island
in the middle of nowhere.

09:42.778 --> 09:45.414
Bummer, you won't get
to read your nerd books

09:45.447 --> 09:48.317
on your Kindle app
while we're on vacation.

09:48.350 --> 09:50.486
I wouldn't mind being able
to post selfies, though.

09:50.519 --> 09:53.823
Books, I downloaded earlier.
You should try reading sometime.

09:53.856 --> 09:57.359
-Hey, city girls.
-You guys wanted to disconnect.

09:57.393 --> 09:59.495
We are disconnected.

09:59.528 --> 10:01.731
<i>I wanted you
to stop checking to see</i>

10:01.764 --> 10:04.266
if he texted every ten seconds.

10:04.300 --> 10:06.203
No, it's, it's,
it's over this time.

10:06.235 --> 10:09.038
-It's done. Over.
-It's fine.

10:09.071 --> 10:11.340
We were just making sure.

10:11.374 --> 10:13.777
Yeah, and anyway,
you're like a crazy nature girl.

10:13.810 --> 10:15.811
You should love this place.

10:15.845 --> 10:17.147
Take a hike in the rain forest

10:17.180 --> 10:19.416
get some samples
for your whatever.

10:19.449 --> 10:21.918
I study environmental science.

10:21.950 --> 10:23.920
-Exactly.
-God.

10:23.952 --> 10:28.191
This place is like
a tropical Tinder island.

10:29.492 --> 10:31.527
Yeah.

10:31.561 --> 10:34.030
Like the saying goes,
"The best way to get over a guy

10:34.062 --> 10:35.532
is to get under another one."

10:35.565 --> 10:37.467
Seriously? Who says that?

10:37.499 --> 10:39.402
And that's exactly
what we're gonna do.

10:39.435 --> 10:41.537
By the end of the week,
you'll have completely

10:41.571 --> 10:44.407
forgotten about that loser.
You didn't even like him anyway.

10:44.440 --> 10:46.910
Okay, well, you constantly
bringing him up

10:46.942 --> 10:50.279
isn't helping anything.

10:50.312 --> 10:53.984
So how about you, Audra? You
could use a little loosening up.

10:54.017 --> 10:56.820
I'm loose, so loose and...
I'm super-loose, guys...

10:56.853 --> 10:59.823
Okay, you should probably
stop saying that.

11:01.456 --> 11:05.195
-Those guys look so...
-Fab?

11:05.228 --> 11:08.799
-Fab and...
-Dumb.

11:08.831 --> 11:10.933
It's not like you have to start
a book club with them.

11:15.037 --> 11:17.807
Domino, Gregory.

11:17.840 --> 11:19.375
Domino, Gregory, come in.

11:24.314 --> 11:27.384
Hello, where are you?
Domino, Gregory!

11:30.119 --> 11:31.888
Have you seen Domino or Gregory?

11:31.921 --> 11:33.989
-Damiano?
-What'd I say?

11:34.023 --> 11:36.359
Yeah, Domino. Damiano, yeah.

11:36.392 --> 11:38.427
I saw them head out to the dock,
like, an hour ago.

11:38.460 --> 11:42.032
-What about you, Jesse?
-No. Why? What's up?

11:44.234 --> 11:45.969
Hey, you, look at me.
Look at me.

11:46.002 --> 11:48.572
What? What?
Go ahead, spit it out.

11:48.604 --> 11:51.340
Damiano hasn't been happy
in a while.

11:51.374 --> 11:54.277
Damiano's not happy.

11:54.310 --> 11:56.946
Well, those idiots better not
have walked off like Neil did.

11:56.979 --> 11:59.081
Unsafe conditions,
lousy accommodations.

11:59.114 --> 12:01.350
What do they think this is,
a luxury resort?

12:01.383 --> 12:02.952
I mean, whatever happened
to two-week notice?

12:02.985 --> 12:04.186
Those damn millennials.

12:04.220 --> 12:05.455
Pretty sure
Damiano is, like, 40.

12:05.488 --> 12:07.457
-Hey, you're not helping.
-Okay.

12:07.489 --> 12:11.327
Listen... we've got
that meet-and-greet coming up.

12:11.360 --> 12:13.362
We've got nothing to eat.
I got it.

12:13.396 --> 12:14.865
Why don't you two
jump back here

12:14.898 --> 12:16.132
open up the fridge
and see if you guys

12:16.165 --> 12:18.268
can throw something together,
okay?

12:18.301 --> 12:20.503
-Really?
-You got a problem with that?

12:20.536 --> 12:23.106
Where's your T-shirt? Where's
your Bodies By Reese T-shirt?

12:23.138 --> 12:24.240
It's in my locker. I'll grab it.

12:24.273 --> 12:25.542
Yeah, I want you to wear that.

12:25.575 --> 12:26.575
You know what?
Actually, scratch that.

12:26.609 --> 12:28.277
Why don't you go fix my boat?

12:28.311 --> 12:29.879
I was trying to start it
this morning, wasn't working.

12:29.912 --> 12:31.013
I know nothing about boats...

12:31.047 --> 12:32.114
But you're a medic, right?

12:32.148 --> 12:33.416
-Yeah.
-Medics fix things.

12:33.449 --> 12:35.151
-Exactly. People.
-And you're a lifeguard.

12:35.183 --> 12:36.452
Which means you deal with things
in the water.

12:36.485 --> 12:37.653
-Right?
-What are you getting at?

12:37.686 --> 12:41.157
Broken boat
in the water. Go fix it.

12:41.190 --> 12:43.292
Please.

12:43.325 --> 12:46.162
-Just go fix the boat.
-Right on it, Reese.

12:46.195 --> 12:48.665
Listen, Erin, I was gonna do
the "Puerto Rico!"

12:48.697 --> 12:51.167
or do you think I should do
"Reese! Reese! Reese"?

12:51.200 --> 12:53.203
-Why...
-You know what?

12:53.235 --> 12:54.670
Don't worry about it.
I'll decide and...

12:54.704 --> 12:56.373
-What's the name of this island?
-Culebrita Island.

12:56.406 --> 12:58.642
-Curberi, Curbi...
-Culebrita.

12:58.675 --> 13:00.243
-You say it.
-Right. Okay.

13:00.276 --> 13:02.378
Okay. It's the one
on the north shore.

13:02.412 --> 13:05.215
-Gotta learn some Spanish, man.
-Positive attitude, guys.

13:05.248 --> 13:08.652
-Positive attitude.
-I hate you.

13:08.685 --> 13:10.520
The guy wearing a scarf
in 90-degree weather

13:10.552 --> 13:12.655
is telling the medic
to go fix the boat.

13:12.689 --> 13:14.291
-Makes a lot of sense.
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

13:14.324 --> 13:16.293
Welcome to Bodies by that guy.

13:16.325 --> 13:18.427
Right now he's got the cook out
looking for stuff to cook.

13:18.460 --> 13:21.330
-Do you see how this works?
-Sadly, I do.

13:21.364 --> 13:22.999
-I'm not doing it.
-I'll be back.

13:23.032 --> 13:24.401
Yup, you do that.

13:24.433 --> 13:28.370
You've got a workout at 3:30.

13:28.403 --> 13:29.672
Safety check.

13:30.440 --> 13:32.075
Fun stuff.

13:54.998 --> 13:57.167
<i>Hey, mami.</i>

13:57.200 --> 13:59.703
-Yeah.
-Hey.

13:59.735 --> 14:01.604
Think this shirt's too tight?

14:01.637 --> 14:04.975
Is that a shirt
or a sausage casing?

14:05.008 --> 14:07.444
Okay, good.
Hey, what do you think?

14:07.476 --> 14:09.378
It looks great, Ryan, yeah.

14:09.412 --> 14:12.415
You know, just don't, like,
flex or bend over

14:12.447 --> 14:14.216
or probably breathe.

14:14.249 --> 14:17.486
Alright.
Hey, bogies coming in.

14:17.519 --> 14:19.555
Hottie at three.

14:19.589 --> 14:21.624
Maverick is engaging.

14:23.026 --> 14:25.362
I'm pretty sure that's 6 p.m.

14:25.394 --> 14:28.030
Yeah, he can't tell time.

14:28.064 --> 14:29.366
Wait, where'd you get
that drink from?

14:29.398 --> 14:31.000
Cabana out front, man. Grab one.

14:31.033 --> 14:34.269
I'll see you at the beach.

14:44.147 --> 14:45.448
My God.
I'm so sorry.

14:45.480 --> 14:47.350
I know, it's totally okay.
I'm so sorry.

14:47.383 --> 14:49.018
And it's totally my fault.

14:49.051 --> 14:51.021
-My...
-God.

14:51.053 --> 14:53.023
-Seriously?
-You've gotta be kidding me.

14:53.056 --> 14:54.490
Did you follow me here?

14:54.523 --> 14:56.158
Why the hell
would I follow you here?

14:56.191 --> 14:57.626
I came here
to get away from you.

14:57.659 --> 14:59.194
I can't even believe this.

14:59.228 --> 15:00.662
I mean, what-what are you
doing here?

15:00.696 --> 15:02.565
-Did somebody set this up?
-Who would set this up?

15:02.598 --> 15:04.601
I don't know, maybe
one of your dumb-ass friends.

15:04.633 --> 15:05.734
Okay, Calm down.

15:05.768 --> 15:08.171
They are not...

15:09.705 --> 15:11.807
Yeah, okay,
you got a small point there.

15:11.840 --> 15:13.542
Yeah, but I don't think
they would do this.

15:13.575 --> 15:16.311
I mean, you are literally
the last person on Earth

15:16.345 --> 15:17.513
that I wanna see right now.

15:17.547 --> 15:19.048
Yeah? Yeah.

15:19.081 --> 15:20.450
'Cause I was really hoping
I'd bump into

15:20.483 --> 15:23.453
my crazy ex-girlfriend
on a deserted island.

15:23.485 --> 15:25.654
-I mean, this is just crazy.
-I'm crazy? Are you kidding?

15:25.687 --> 15:27.723
I'm sorry, Sam,
that I have emotions

15:27.757 --> 15:29.792
something that you don't know
anything about!

15:29.825 --> 15:33.229
Yeah, right. Emotional, crazy.
Tomato, tomahto.

15:33.262 --> 15:34.696
-Right, Eden?
-Okay.

15:34.729 --> 15:36.166
We're leaving, we're leaving.

15:36.199 --> 15:37.434
-Good.
-We have to go. We have to go.

15:37.466 --> 15:38.801
-We have to go.
-Did you forget?

15:38.835 --> 15:40.235
We're stuck here for a week.

15:40.268 --> 15:42.272
We have to kayak back alone.

15:42.305 --> 15:44.074
We can't just go, Eden.

15:44.106 --> 15:46.508
Plus, there's this guy, Mark.
He's really cute.

15:46.542 --> 15:48.644
